Citation.sTitle: Vapor-Liquid Equilibria in Binary Systems Formed by n-Hexane with Alcohols
Citation.sAbstract: The modified witoslawski ebulliometer was used for the accurate determination of vapor-liquid equilibria in binary isothermal systems formed by n-hexane with the following: 2-butanol at (313.15, 323.15, and 333.15) K, 2-pentanol at (313.15, 323.15, 333.15, and 338.15) K, and 2-methyl-2-butanol at (313.15, 323.15, 333.15, and 338.15) K. The vapor pressures of the pure substances are also given. The experimental data have been compared with literature data (if available) of those systems and correlated by means of the Redlich-Kister, nonrandom two-liquid (NRTL), and Wilson equations.
